  "text": "There are some factors affecting membrane fouling that exist in the feed liquid. In general, the direct method of controlling the characteristics of the feed liquid is to add a flocculant or adsorbent to the feed liquid. Compared with the monomer salt, the polymeric salt can provide more positive charge and electrically neutralize the suspended particles in the liquid, which can improve the removal rate of the suspended particles and increase the diameter of the particles [CITATION_1] . The indirect method is to control the reaction by changing the sedimentation and flocculation performance of the feed liquid by adjusting the operating conditions such as HRT, SRT and reaction temperature.",
  "correct_citation": {
